  console.log(`${v.label}: ${v.range_min}-${v.range_max} (w=${v.weight})`);
});
</code></pre> <p>Using with Feasibility</p> <p>The intervention config defines the default filters used by the feasibility calculation. When you POST to <code>/api/calculate-feasibility</code> with just <code>{"intervention": "Organic Farming"}</code>, the system fetches this config and uses its variables as filters. You can override these by passing custom <code>filters</code> in the POST body.</p> <p>Data Range vs Filter Range</p> <p><code>data_min</code>/<code>data_max</code> are the actual min/max across all blocks. <code>range_min</code>/<code>range_max</code> are the acceptable thresholds for feasibility scoring. Blocks with values inside the range score positively; blocks outside score zero for that variable.</p>

